🚀 JPA kya hota hai?
👉 JPA = Java Persistence API

🧠 Simple Samajh
JPA ek specification (rules) hai jo batata hai
-> Java objects ko database me kaise store karna hai

⚠️ IMPORTANT
👉 JPA khud kuch nahi karta ❌
👉 Hibernate karta hai ✅

- JPA = rules
- Hibernate = implementation

🔥 Real Relation
JPA → Hibernate → JDBC → Database


🧩 JPA ka kaam kya hai?
👉 Tu object banata hai:

User user = new User();
user.setName("Pulkit");

👉 JPA + Hibernate isko convert karta hai:
INSERT INTO user ...

⚙️ JPA me tu kya karta hai?
1️. Entity banata hai:

@Entity
public class User {
    @Id
    private int id;
    private String name;
}

👉 Ye table ban gaya automatically

2️. Repository use karta hai

public interface UserRepository extends JpaRepository<User, Integer> {
}

👉 Ab tu likh sakta hai:

userRepository.save(user);
userRepository.findAll();

🔥 Internally kya hota hai?

👉 Tu likhta hai:

userRepository.save(user);

👉 Hibernate karta hai:

INSERT INTO user ...


**************************************************************************
Apn ne jo code likhe uska explaination:

🧩 PART 1: ENTITY CLASS
@Entity
public class UserClassHibernate {

👉 Matlab:
“Ye class DB ki table banegi”

🔑 Fields
@Id
@GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY)
private Long id;

👉 Ye kya kar raha hai:
@Id → Primary key
@GeneratedValue → Auto increment

👉 DB khud id dega
private String name;
👉 Simple column

🏗️ Constructors

public UserClassHibernate() {}
👉 Mandatory hai (Hibernate ko chahiye)

public UserClassHibernate(String name) {
    this.name = name;
}
👉 Object banane ke liye


🧩 PART 2: JPAUtil (Engine Setup)

private static final EntityManagerFactory emf;

👉 Ye ek factory hai
👉 EntityManager banata hai

⚙️ Static Block
emf = Persistence.createEntityManagerFactory("myJpaUnit");

👉 Ye load karta hai:
- DB config
- Hibernate settings

👉 "myJpaUnit" → persistence.xml me defined hota hai

🔄 Method
public static EntityManager getEntityManager() {
    return emf.createEntityManager();
}

👉 Ye deta hai:
DB se baat karne ka tool


🧩 PART 3: MAIN LOGIC
EntityManager em = JPAUtil.getEntityManager();

👉 Ye mila:
DB handle karne ka object

🔥 Step 1: Object bana
UserClassHibernate user = new UserClassHibernate("Alice");

👉 Abhi sirf Java object hai
👉 DB me nahi gaya

🔥 Step 2: Transaction start
em.getTransaction().begin();

👉 Bol raha:
“Ab DB operation start”

🔥 Step 3: Save (IMPORTANT)
em.persist(user);

👉 Ye karta hai:
INSERT INTO user_class_hibernate (name) VALUES ('Alice');

👉 SAME as:
userRepository.save(user);

🔥 Step 4: Commit
em.getTransaction().commit();

👉 Bol raha:
“Save permanently”

👉 Agar commit nahi:
❌ DB me kuch nahi jayega

🔥 Step 5: Print
System.out.println(user.getId());

👉 Ab id aa jayegi (auto-generated)

🔥 Step 6: Close
em.close();
JPAUtil.close();

👉 Resources free

🔥 FULL FLOW (IMPORTANT)
1. EntityManager lo
2. Object banao
3. Transaction start
4. persist() → save
5. commit()
6. close


| Thing         | Meaning    |
| ------------- | ---------- |
| Entity        | Table      |
| EntityManager | DB handler |
| persist()     | save       |
| Transaction   | safety     |
| commit()      | final save |
